text: You would test if the value of the hubdb table rows call is empty.

I want to show the google map restaurants locations on map with marker.
I am use this code from here <https://designers.HubSpot.com/docs/tutorials/lets-build-a-page-with-a-map-with-hubdb>

But in my browser code it's showing empty values from browser query string <https://prnt.sc/12w71c6>
I have use
```{{ request.query_dict['lat'] }}```
this code to print the value from query string from browsers. It's working in here <https://prnt.sc/12w7gwg>
Showing empty
So... `request.query_dict['lat']` is reading the URL so <https://www.google.com/?lat=1234>
if you are using a preview URL append it with `&lat=1234`
otherwise, you can put in your own values either from a browser ask or an IP lookup
